rder to support business decision making. Most of the exercises use Excel, today’s most common analysis tool, and R, a popular analytic computer environment. The techniques covered range from the most basic text analytics, such as key word analysis, to more sophisticated techniques, such as topic extraction and text similarity scoring. Companion files with numerous datasets are included for use with case studies and exercises. FEATURES: Organized by tool or technique, with the basic techniques presented first and the more sophisticated techniques presented laterUses Excel and R for datasets in case studies and exercisesFeatures the CRISP-DM data mining standard with early chapters for conducting the preparatory steps in data miningCompanion files with numerous datasets and figures from the text.The companion files are available online by emailing the publisher with proof of purchase at info@merclearning.com.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aDecision makingxData processingvCase studies. 4aData. 4aHuman Resource Management. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Business Communication / General.2bisacsh  aBusiness Communication.  aComputer Science.  aData Analytics.  aData Visualization.  aExcel.  aR.0 cEPUBz97816839266410 cprintz978168392666540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168392665840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781683926658423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781683926658/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles